  "notes": "SMO S40 as orchestrator for up to 4 outdoor slave heat pumps. Covers S2125 / F2120 / F2040 (they share the same slave register layout). Base = SMO S40 master + common S-series holding registers (setpoints, alarms, energy). Slave sets = 16 compressor/refrigerant diagnostics per position, repeated for slaves 1-4 with model-independent addresses (301/300/299/298 → 1805/1791/1777/1763). Does NOT cover: (1) F1345/F1355 ground-source HPs (the PDF documents these as slaves of an S1X55 master, not SMO S40 — unverified whether SMO supports them); (2) standalone NIBE controllers S1155/S1156/S1255/S1256, S735/S735C, or F2040 used in standalone mode — those need their own templates. IDs cross-validated against the manufacturer PDF but not a live unit; verify before first production commissioning, especially the common S-series registers at IDs 11/20/22/26/30/34/38 where the same ID can differ between product families.",
